e, defensible operating model instead of stacking a dozen half-rules. I\u2019m glad we pushed past one-variable tweaks, because the combined view is materially better than any single change alone.\n\n**Decision:**\n- New leading deploy candidate:\n  - **Active hours:** `[11, 12, 19]`\n  - **Bias threshold:** `45` for 11h/12h, `55` for 19h\n  - **Block 19h trades tagged `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` or `BOOST`**\n  - **Drop 20h entirely**\n  - Churn filter remains conceptually valid, but it does not currently alter the keep-set beyond the above rules.\n- This is now strong enough to justify being turned into a formal deploy spec or code patch next cycle.\n\n**Next:** Convert this exact combined configuration into a deploy-ready patch/spec for `trading_bot.py`, then shadow-validate it against the next full active day before pushing live.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 20:46 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] 20h Session Fails the Keep-Test\n\n**Task:** Re-evaluate whether 20h still deserves to be an active PM trading hour using the enriched Apr 1+ dataset plus tonight\u2019s live 20h tape.\n**Finding:**\n",
